    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "When you say a \"challenge to established political coalitions\" and \"testing the resilience\" of institutions, it sounds like you might be implying there's a risk of friction or even fragmentation. Some commentators argue that rapid demographic shifts can dilute the traditional cultural values that hold these democratic systems together. In your analysis, is there a risk that this shift could lead to a loss of institutional stability or a push toward more radical, less predictable governance styles?",
