      "content": "While rapid demographic shifts create inevitable political friction, framing it as an inherent risk of instability overlooks the adaptive nature of democracies. Instead of a guaranteed fragmentation, this pressure forces institutional evolution, requiring political parties to broaden their appeal and incorporate new perspectives. The \"test\" is less about collapse and more about whether existing political structures can successfully integrate diverse interests into functioning governance processes.",
